  "texts": [
    "Bochinski et al. (2018) proposed Cost-Effective Active Learning (CEAL) (Wang et al. 2016) for plankton recognition.",
    "In contrast to traditional active learning where only the manually annotated samples are used in the model training, CEAL utilizes also the unlabeled high-confidence samples for training with class predictions as pseudo labels.",
    "Haug et al. (2021b); Haug (2021); Haug et al. (2021a) proposed Combined Informative and Representative Active Learning technique (CIRAL) to minimize the human involvement in the plankton image labeling process.",
    "The main idea behind the method is to find the images with minimal perturbations that are often miss-classified and ignore the images that are far from the decision boundary.",
    "The DeepFool algorithm is used to compute small perturbations to the images."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Bochinski et al. (2018) proposed Cost-Effective Active Learning (CEAL) (Wang et al. 2016) for plankton recognition.",
    "Haug et al. (2021b); Haug (2021); Haug et al. (2021a) proposed Combined Informative and Representative Active Learning technique (CIRAL) to minimize the human involvement in the plankton image labeling process."
  ]
